An example of an Outlook Calendar with such a parameter is as per attached [Feierabend Termin.ics|https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/attachment/151682/Feierabend%20Termin.ics]. Import the calendar into TeamCal, and notice that the event that is supposed to show up on 13th February 2015 is not shown at all. The event is, however, added correctly into the *ao_950dc3_tc_events* table in the database, with the correct RECURRENCE_ID_TIMESTAMP

h3.Workaround
Remove this line from the file:
{code}
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID="W. Europe Standard Time":20150213T160000
{code}
Save the ICS file again, then reimport the file into Team Calendars. The event should now show up. We can opt to replace this parameter with the RRULE parameter instead, described here: http://www.mattnworb.com/post/21850303360/how-to-get-ical-to-recognize-recurring-events-in

